******
[1] ECDC update
Date: Thu 14 Jul 2011
Source: European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC)
[edited]
http://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/activities/sciadvice/Lists/ECDC%20Reviews/ECDC_DispForm.aspx?List=512ff74f%2D77d4%2D4ad8%2Db6d6%2Dbf0f23083f30&ID=1148&RootFolder=%2Fen%2Factivities%2Fsciadvice%2FLists%2FECDC%20Reviews


Wed 13 Jul 2011
---------------
As of today, 13 Jul 2011, the cumulative number of STEC [Shiga toxin
producing _Escherichia coli_] O104:H4 cases in the EU/EEA is 3848.
This includes 763 HUS [hemolytic uremic syndrome] STEC cases and 3 085
non-HUS STEC cases. In total, 44 infected persons have died, of which
28 were HUS STEC cases and 16 were non-HUS STEC cases.

In Germany, since the last update, 1 HUS STEC case and 8 non-HUS STEC
cases have been reported. Within the last 10 days (3-12 Jul 2011), 3
HUS STEC cases and 9 non-HUS STEC cases fell ill. The last known date
of illness onset in a patient with confirmed STEC O104 was 1 Jul 2011.
The last reported date of illness onset among all cases was 4 Jul
2011.

Thu 14 Jul 2011
---------------
As of today, 14 Jul 2011, the cumulative number of probable and
confirmed STEC cases in the EU/EEA is 3867. This includes 762 HUS STEC
cases and 3 105 non-HUS STEC cases. In total, 44 infected persons have
died, of which 28 were HUS STEC cases and 16 were non-HUS STEC cases.

In Germany, since the last update, 1 HUS STEC case has been excluded,
and 20 non-HUS STEC cases have been reported. Within the last 10 days
(4-13 July), 1 HUS STEC case and 8 non-HUS STEC cases fell ill. The
last known date of illness onset in a patient with confirmed STEC O104
was 7 Jul 2011. This was also the last reported date of illness onset
among all cases.

--
